<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Cayleu on 03-26-2001 12:41 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Level 56:

Remedy
C-Heal
Celheal
DL
alt1
alt2
DA 
DB

At low levels, you could get away with not having DA/DB, but up to a point, DA/DB is so valuable I can not imagine any cleric not memming them. Forget about your own life, your saving your group with these, since cleric dead = doomed. Sometimes on a massive pull, its going to take a few seconds for the chanter to mes everything. My AC is good, but critters in Velious still hit dang hard, and sometimes a momentary cleric-mobbing that would kill me is something the group can live with just fine, if only I could buy them an extra few seconds, where if I didnt have invuln up for that short time, I would be dead, and they would have to evac or die with me.

For alts, I usually use the cheapo stuns, stun and holy might. I am not interested in blowing more mana for some damage, stuns are to paralize or interrupt the critter, and this does that just fine.

Buffing, I switch in and out HB, Symbols, etc

Sometimes when a group is so good I'm always fom or bored, I might mem a nuke. For critters that are going to have a DS, I mem MoK

Keeping Gate memmed is a simple waste of a spell spot, you can go invuln, med gate, and stand up to cast (and I can cast through darned near anything if I have a corner to stand in) I am not going to gate out on a group unless the group is dead, or its hopeless. (and by hopeless, I really do mean no chance at all, like 4 frogs in sebilis, chanter LD, evaccer dead, and the tanks telling me to get out.)</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
